<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5962] Internationalize error messages for database decryption</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5962</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some of the error messages for database decryption (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5792&quot; title=&quot;Make it possible to turn off encryption on an already encrypted database.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-5792&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-5792&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) are not fully internationalized, as they take a hard-coded English message as an argument. We should make the messages come from messages.xml so that they can be localized.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As discussed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5792&quot; title=&quot;Make it possible to turn off encryption on an already encrypted database.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-5792&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-5792&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we may also want to merge the messages for encryption, re-encryption and decryption to reduce the total number of messages.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
